-- Uganda Electricity Distribution Returns to Profit in Full Year to December
-- B y   F r e d   O j a m b o
-- 2010-10-22T06:36:21Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-22/uganda-electricity-distribution-returns-to-profit-in-full-year-to-december.html
Uganda Electricity Distribution Co.,
a state-owned company, returned to profitability in 
2009 after it wrote off less bad debt.  Net income in the year through December amounted to 13.4
billion shillings, compared with a loss of 22.7 billion a year
earlier, the Kampala-based company said in an advertisement
published today in New Vision newspaper.  Losses on debt write-offs fell to 406.7 million shillings,
from 13 billion shillings in 2008, the company said.  Revenue rose 14 percent to 38.1 billion shillings, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Fred Ojambo in Kampala at 
 fojambo@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
